Why Does This Work?

Consider:

s = "waterbottle"

All rotations are:

waterbottle
aterbottlew
terbottlewa
...

When we concatenate:

waterbottlewaterbottle

every possible rotation appears as a contiguous substring.

Therefore:

goal is a rotation of s
⇔
goal is a substring of (s + s)
